counterharm_basic:
When you’re settin’ up a website, you want to make sure the mob feels welcome right from the start.
<?php
// This bit here is your controller lookin’ after the welcome yarn
namespace App\Controller;

use Symfony\Bundle\FrameworkBundle\Controller\AbstractController;
use Symfony\Component\HttpFoundation\Response;
use Symfony\Component\Routing\Annotation\Route;

class WelcomeController extends AbstractController
{
    // This road brings folks over to the welcome spot
    #[Route('/welcome', name: 'welcome')]
    public function index(): Response
    {
        // Here’s the message for all our people droppin’ in
        return new Response('<h1>Welcome to Country, everyone!</h1>');
    }
}

That code helps you say g’day to all the mob, keepin’ things open and friendly for anyone stoppin’ by.

